Decision Boundary: The model predicts class 1 if the output probability is above a certain threshold (commonly 0.5); otherwise, it predicts class 0. This threshold creates a decision boundary separating the two classes.â€‹

Model Training: It estimates the coefficients (ğ›½) by maximizing the likelihood function, a method known as Maximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE). This approach finds the parameters that make the observed data most probable.


